metadata.name: Ecce Gratum #31
metadata.description:
"Ecce Gratum" is a symphony of colors and lines, a visual work that sings to the soul. The strokes of the brush are bold and confident, yet gentle and loving, like the notes of a symphony. The title, "Ecce Gratum", translates to "Behold the pleasing", and as you gaze upon this art, it is impossible not to be moved by its beauty and wonder. This painting is a celebration of life, a reminder to embrace the present and to find joy in the simple things. It is a call to look beyond the surface, to see the beauty in the world around us, and to let our hearts sing

[S] on live view to save a png

metadata.name: (Un)priced #119
metadata.description:
The idea is to create a sketch-like work of art that, in addition to beauty, has a unique function. Each mint is a roadmap for the pricing of subsequent sales.

Each mint consists of several squares filled with a random sequence of numbers.
Each of the numbers inside the square, from left to right, determines the next price of the mint. So the rule is simple, check the previous price, use the number inside the square for pricing.  If, for any reason, the pricing is different from the specified numbers, the next price of the work will be determined according to the increase factor of the numbers inside the squares.
Each of the miners also receives a percentage of future sales.

Press ‚Äôs‚Äô on the live mode to save the artwork.

Made with p5js.

metadata.name: Pixilex #22
metadata.description:
Pixelated Generative Art Work based on Hydra LIVE CODING VIDEO SYNTH.

https://hydra.ojack.xyz/

The Generative Tokens are produced only using 10 lines of code

/////////////===================================/////////////////////

 osc(26, 0, 1)
  .saturate(.33)
  .blend(0.25)
  .modulateKaleid(osc(20, 5, 3), 0.66)
  .luma(0.174)
  .rotate(10,0)
  .modulate(o0, () =>5.5)
  .scale(1.2)
  .pixelate(30,40)
  .out(o0);

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

metadata.name: Tilemoji #27
metadata.description:
This collection of low resolution generative art is presented using emojis rather than an image, so it can be copied like normal text. You are also welcome to take a screenshot for sharing or printing. Most results are designed to fit in a 280 character tweet, except for rare extra large variants. There are five different generative algorithms possible, each with their own set of parameters. Emojis are rendered using the Twemoji font and may look different in some environments.

Thank you for supporting my work during the first year of fxhash. For me it has been a life changing experience. I am forever grateful for all of the art and friendships we've created. Many of us have met on social media, so I developed this special project with a fun way to display and share. Congrats to artists, collectors, and developers for an amazing year!

This work is part of the fxhash anniversary event (#fxhashturnsone)
All of primary sale proceeds will go to Save Pakistan

metadata.name: L-Template #512
metadata.description:
THIS IS NOT AN ARTWORK.

Instead: a framework to store artwork data components onchain by including them as features in the token's smart contract. The stored data are parameters of a Lindenmayer System, which is a formal grammar that was initially conceived of as a theory of plant growth. L-Systems can model complex forms of plants using relatively few simple rules. Custom rules are generated during the minting of each token, based on the transaction hash string. 

The idea is that each iteration of the artwork can be reproduced accurately using an L-System interpreter by accessing the tezos blockchain through the FxHash API (GraphQL) and interpreting token metadata.

Reusable template source: https://github.com/x-terrain/x-terrain.github.io/tree/main/L-Template

Part of an ongoing project with RefractionDAO

metadata.name: Blotto! #509
metadata.description:
Vanilla JS + SVG
November 2022

Edition of 365

The starting point for this piece was an attempt to simulate the effect of dropping coloured inks or paints onto wet or dry paper ("blots") by combining mixed gradients and various levels of svg filters. I then added stroke and fine line drawings to the blots and played around with rotation and opacity and leaving blanks in the grids. 

The results range from minimal smooth circles, sometimes fading away into the background, to noisy splashes or clouds.

The defined features of the project are:

Blot palettes: 9+n (1 is generated randomly)
Blotting paper: 6 colours
Blot grid: 5 layouts (1x1, 3x3, 5x5, 10x10, 20x20)
Blot stroke: true/false
Blot blanks: true/false
Blotted lines: true/false
Blotulence! (extra turbulence): true/false

To save a PNG file, press "P" or save an SVG by pressing "S"

This project has been tested and works in Chrome, Brave, Edge and Firefox (a little slower on the latter, so please be patient). It does not work in Safari or on IOS at this time.

// PRIMARY SALES
If/when the project mints out, 50% of primary will be donated to Girls Who Code Canada (https://girlswhocode.com/en-ca) and the other 50% to Breakfast Club Canada and I will post the donation receipts on the fx(hash) Discord as well as on my Twitter & genart.social.
